How did you know it's
my birthday?

610
01:15:18,493 --> 01:15:19,782
Didn't you mention it?

611
01:15:21,223 --> 01:15:22,782
I am so happy today

612
01:15:24,163 --> 01:15:28,122
Guess what? Esha called me

613
01:15:31,503 --> 01:15:33,302
She is coming to see me today

614
01:15:35,473 --> 01:15:36,902
My daughter is coming here...

615
01:15:48,883 --> 01:15:51,152
Sid, she remembered it's
my birthday today

616
01:15:54,863 --> 01:15:57,982
I'll be seeing her after 5 years!

617
01:15:59,563 --> 01:16:02,322
I've cooked everything myself.
I baked a cake

618
01:16:04,633 --> 01:16:05,832
I'm so happy

619
01:16:06,373 --> 01:16:08,992
Is Esha coming alone or your...

620
01:16:09,443 --> 01:16:14,502
Oh no. She told him she's going to
a friend's birthday party...

621
01:16:14,873 --> 01:16:18,672
Because Ajay will never let her
come here

622
01:16:22,623 --> 01:16:23,582
Would you like to meet her?

623
01:16:26,193 --> 01:16:26,852
It'll make me happy

624
01:16:34,563 --> 01:16:38,192
How dare you teach my daughter
to lie? Have you no shame?

625
01:16:40,573 --> 01:16:44,372
Thank God I heard Esha
talk to you over the phone

626
01:16:44,743 --> 01:16:46,712
Why don't you stay away from her?

627
01:16:47,413 --> 01:16:48,702
I am her mother!

628
01:16:49,143 --> 01:16:52,542
You were her mother but now
Kiran is her mother

629
01:16:53,253 --> 01:16:55,042
It'd be wise of you to understand
this

630
01:16:55,583 --> 01:16:58,212
Don't ever try to meet Esha again

631
01:16:58,753 --> 01:17:01,052
Not unless you want me to take
you to court... again

632
01:17:02,423 --> 01:17:03,862
You understand what I'm getting at,
don't you?

633
01:17:46,473 --> 01:17:48,272
He tells me I am not Esha's mother!

634
01:17:48,473 --> 01:17:49,442
That Esha is not my daughter!

635
01:17:49,643 --> 01:17:56,272
I am her mother...

636
01:18:01,583 --> 01:18:02,852
He married again

637
01:18:03,993 --> 01:18:07,442
He destroyed all my dreams.
I said nothing

638
01:18:09,263 --> 01:18:11,282
Because I had everything...

639
01:18:13,363 --> 01:18:14,122
I had my Esha

640
01:18:23,613 --> 01:18:24,802
I have nothing at all

641
01:18:25,943 --> 01:18:34,512
I am nothing. Nothing.

642
01:18:57,243 --> 01:19:02,042
You know, crying doesn't suit
you at all

643
01:19:04,383 --> 01:19:05,852
What else can I do!

644
01:19:09,053 --> 01:19:10,352
You can come with me

645
01:20:05,213 --> 01:20:08,902
You two must be wondering where
Siddharth has brought you!

646
01:20:09,113 --> 01:20:11,742
No such thing. We'd go
anywhere to eat cake

647
01:20:19,523 --> 01:20:20,582
Will you dance with me?

648
01:20:22,833 --> 01:20:25,992
Where?
- Right here there's lot of space, come.

649
01:21:21,353 --> 01:21:22,322
Sid, we've reached your house

650
01:21:27,523 --> 01:21:28,992
What?

651
01:21:36,033 --> 01:21:37,162
You're joking, right?

652
01:21:42,203 --> 01:21:43,832
Hey Akash, he's serious man!

653
01:21:45,143 --> 01:21:46,512
Have you gone mad?

654
01:21:53,453 --> 01:21:55,852
Sid, my knowledge of such
things is a bit sad but...

655
01:21:56,553 --> 01:21:57,982
...this is a but much, isn't it?

656
01:22:00,763 --> 01:22:02,952
Is that because she's older?

657
01:22:03,393 --> 01:22:05,692
No. I mean that too

658
01:22:08,003 --> 01:22:09,692
Wait a minute! Why are we even
discussing this nonsense?

659
01:22:13,503 --> 01:22:16,372
Because I thought that may be
you guys would understand

660
01:22:22,843 --> 01:22:25,542
Hey Sid! Understand what?

661
01:22:27,753 --> 01:22:31,382
You say you love a woman who
is 10 to 15 years older than you...

662
01:22:31,953 --> 01:22:34,892
...has a daughter, had a husband

663
01:22:35,963 --> 01:22:38,222
You've told us she has a
drinking problem

664
01:22:38,433 --> 01:22:39,552
What should we understand?
- Just this...

665
01:22:40,003 --> 01:22:42,052
I know all this and still
love her

666
01:22:42,703 --> 01:22:46,532
But Sid, think about it.
This isn't love, it's insanity

667
01:22:46,743 --> 01:22:49,402
No. This is love

668
01:22:52,443 --> 01:22:54,742
I don't expect her to be mine
or marry me

669
01:22:55,113 --> 01:22:56,412
I don't expect any such thing

670
01:22:57,413 --> 01:22:59,742
Even if she doesn't love me,
it's okay because I...

671
01:22:59,953 --> 01:23:03,252
okay! I get it

672
01:23:04,553 --> 01:23:07,752
Remember, Sameer? Even I had
started off like this

673
01:23:08,563 --> 01:23:12,022
Started what off?
Oh. Of course.

674
01:23:12,233 --> 01:23:16,102
Okay, Sid. If that's what it's about
then I have no objection

675
01:23:16,733 --> 01:23:18,432
In fact she's perfect for you

676
01:23:18,833 --> 01:23:23,102
She's experienced, lives alone.
You visit her everyday

677
01:23:24,913 --> 01:23:27,102
Learn from him, Sameer

678
01:23:27,443 --> 01:23:29,772
Really, Sid. You couldn't have
chosen better...

679
01:23:34,723 --> 01:23:36,622
How disgusting can you get!

680
01:23:39,793 --> 01:23:43,992
Here I am telling you I love her and
you make it sound so sick and dirty

681
01:23:49,133 --> 01:23:51,792
We don't have to approve
everything our friends do

682
01:23:53,303 --> 01:23:55,632
But there is a line in every
friendship that shouldn't be crossed

683
01:23:55,843 --> 01:23:57,272
And you have crossed it today

684
01:24:02,683 --> 01:24:06,582
At some point in life everyone
experiences true love

685
01:24:08,783 --> 01:24:12,312
Then all the things you said...
about her age and stuff...

686
01:24:13,963 --> 01:24:18,022
They don't mean anything.
They all seem trivial

687
01:24:21,933 --> 01:24:23,422
You won't understand this today

688
01:24:26,203 --> 01:24:27,502
But some day you will know...

689
01:24:27,703 --> 01:24:29,572
You don't decide to fall in love

690
01:24:31,343 --> 01:24:32,312
It just happens

691
01:24:39,213 --> 01:24:40,342
Are you finished?

692
01:24:50,563 --> 01:24:51,392
Sameer, are you coming?

693
01:25:40,300 --> 01:25:41,559
I still remember that night

694
01:25:49,709 --> 01:25:52,008
I never thought things would go
that far

695
01:25:58,419 --> 01:25:59,508
I couldn't sleep all night

696
01:26:01,089 --> 01:26:02,578
I went and met Akash
the next morning

697
01:26:42,528 --> 01:26:44,357
These things happen
between friends

698
01:26:44,828 --> 01:26:48,157
Let's go meet Sid.
He must be feeling bad too

699
01:26:50,437 --> 01:26:52,336
You're sure to run into him
somewhere

700
01:26:52,737 --> 01:26:55,536
What'll you do? Ignore him?

701
01:27:02,147 --> 01:27:03,336
You're coming to meet Sid

702
01:27:05,887 --> 01:27:07,006
Leave me alone, Sameer!

703
01:27:33,606 --> 01:27:34,575
I have to see Sid

704
01:27:34,906 --> 01:27:35,805
He's gone

705
01:27:36,016 --> 01:27:37,775
Where? - Kasauli

706
01:27:38,176 --> 01:27:43,045
They called yesterday to say his
application was accepted. So he...

707
01:27:46,056 --> 01:27:49,355
What is it, Sameer?
Is everything alright?

708
01:27:51,596 --> 01:27:54,455
Of course. I should go

709
01:28:01,505 --> 01:28:04,804
I didn't realise that things
would never be the same again

710
01:28:05,705 --> 01:28:10,114
You went to Kasauli... A week later,
Akash left for Australia

711
01:28:21,725 --> 01:28:22,954
Take care of yourself

712
01:28:23,495 --> 01:28:26,654
You remember the name of the man
who'll receive you in Sydney?

713
01:28:26,865 --> 01:28:29,984
Mr. Mehta... Relax, Dad.
I remember

714
01:28:35,634 --> 01:28:37,833
Bye. I'll call you from there

715
01:28:41,474 --> 01:28:43,403
I must tell you something
- What's it?

716
01:28:45,344 --> 01:28:52,213
I always made fun of your
endless romantic entanglements

717
01:28:54,424 --> 01:28:57,783
Never stopped to think how you
must feel

718
01:29:00,094 --> 01:29:03,253
You know I was just kidding,
don't you?

719
01:29:06,964 --> 01:29:07,993
Don't worry about it

720
01:29:08,663 --> 01:29:10,062
You weren't the only one who was
kidding

721
01:29:11,603 --> 01:29:12,692
You remember Shalini?

722
01:29:14,173 --> 01:29:16,662
I remember Shalini...
And Rohit's punch as well

723
01:29:18,073 --> 01:29:19,802
I knew she was Rohit's fiancee

724
01:29:22,083 --> 01:29:24,102
Why didn't you tell me?
Why didn't you stop me?

725
01:29:51,572 --> 01:29:52,511
I said Hi

726
01:29:56,382 --> 01:29:57,311
Where are you going?

727
01:29:59,222 --> 01:30:00,651
This flight goes to Sydney

728
01:30:01,382 --> 01:30:02,411
But where are you going?

729
01:30:05,222 --> 01:30:07,381
How strange! All three of us
are going to Sydney

730
01:30:08,622 --> 01:30:09,091
Three?

731
01:30:09,492 --> 01:30:11,151
Sure. You, me, and this flight

732
01:30:15,402 --> 01:30:16,991
You do know you're insane,
don't you?

733
01:30:25,741 --> 01:30:28,680
I'm really sorry about
the other night

734
01:30:30,251 --> 01:30:31,140
I was just kidding

735
01:30:39,721 --> 01:30:40,210
So what are you...

736
01:30:44,061 --> 01:30:45,580
What are you doing in Sydney?

737
01:30:46,661 --> 01:30:49,290
Dad has a business there he
wants me to manage...

738
01:30:50,001 --> 01:30:52,900
Let's see how long it lasts now.
And you?

739
01:30:54,040 --> 01:30:55,199
My uncle lives there

740
01:30:55,640 --> 01:30:57,939
My mother's brother.
I'm visiting him

741
01:30:58,470 --> 01:30:59,369
He's nothing like Rohit, is he!

742
01:31:03,810 --> 01:31:04,469
What does he do?

743
01:31:08,220 --> 01:31:09,409
Have you been to Sydney before?

744
01:31:11,550 --> 01:31:13,109
Do you always ask so many
questions?

745
01:31:13,660 --> 01:31:15,949
Yes. Have you been to Sydney
before?

746
01:31:16,760 --> 01:31:17,229
Yes

747
01:31:18,790 --> 01:31:20,189
Good. You can show me around

748
01:31:20,730 --> 01:31:23,959
Wait a minute. Don't you know
anybody else there?

749
01:31:24,800 --> 01:31:26,029
Of course. There is a Mr. Mehta

750
01:31:27,869 --> 01:31:29,838
And won't it be fun hanging out
with him?

751
01:31:34,479 --> 01:31:35,378
I said I'm sorry

752
01:31:36,109 --> 01:31:38,338
Okay but I will have to ask
my uncle

753
01:31:40,519 --> 01:31:42,108
But he won't refuse.

754
01:31:42,749 --> 01:31:43,218
Why?

755
01:31:43,989 --> 01:31:45,248
Because I have bought him a gift!

756
01:32:18,018 --> 01:32:20,177
I'm fine but please stop
calling me uncle now

757
01:32:20,388 --> 01:32:22,717
You've grown up which makes us
practically the same age

758
01:32:34,038 --> 01:32:35,127
So, is it a business trip?

759
01:32:35,337 --> 01:32:39,096
We have an export business and
Dad's exported me here to handle it

760
01:32:39,307 --> 01:32:41,036
Exports? Sounds very boring, man

761
01:32:41,247 --> 01:32:42,076
That's what I think too

762
01:32:42,647 --> 01:32:44,666
Personally, I prefer something more
adventurous...

763
01:32:45,417 --> 01:32:46,606
...like wild life photography

764
01:32:46,987 --> 01:32:48,246
You like photography?

765
01:32:49,217 --> 01:32:53,586
Mum says the first word I said
wasn't Papa or Mama...

766
01:32:53,787 --> 01:32:54,616
It was camera!

767
01:32:58,897 --> 01:32:59,356
I'm Steve

768
01:33:00,427 --> 01:33:02,056
Steve? - Satyadev Mehta

769
01:33:04,837 --> 01:33:08,426
I've organized a car for you.
I'll get your trolley

770
01:33:10,906 --> 01:33:12,765
Okay Shalini, I'll take your leave.
Bye, Mahesh

771
01:33:14,576 --> 01:33:20,065
Here's my card. If you need
anything in Sydney, call me

772
01:33:47,005 --> 01:33:49,774
Well, I'd better leave now.
I'm sure you want to rest

773
01:33:50,115 --> 01:33:52,074
I'll send the driver to pick you
up tomorrow

774
01:34:15,665 --> 01:34:19,004
Yes, I'll tell Mr. Mehta

775
01:34:46,534 --> 01:34:49,023
Dad wants you to send him
a copy of the new contract

776
01:34:52,403 --> 01:34:53,732
You are coming to the meeting
tomorrow, aren't you?

777
01:34:55,103 --> 01:34:57,402
Can you give me our transaction
file?

778
01:34:57,673 --> 01:34:59,302
I'd like to know a little more about
them before the meeting

779
01:34:59,643 --> 01:35:01,112
I'll send you the file right away

780
01:35:06,983 --> 01:35:08,452
Is there a good restaurant around
here?

781
01:35:34,742 --> 01:35:36,771
Being alone in a new city
can be so boring

782
01:35:37,552 --> 01:35:38,811
But you aren't alone!

783
01:35:39,512 --> 01:35:40,711
Who said I was bored?

784
01:35:45,222 --> 01:35:47,151
Who'd have thought that
someday you

785
01:35:47,362 --> 01:35:49,221
and me would be sitting
here like friends

786
01:35:51,832 --> 01:35:52,851
Especially after all that happened...

787
01:35:56,002 --> 01:35:56,621
So how is Rohit?

788
01:35:58,172 --> 01:36:00,601
He's fine. I spoke to him
this morning

789
01:36:01,701 --> 01:36:05,260
I told him I met you on the flight
and...

790
01:36:08,811 --> 01:36:10,670
And he doesn't like you meeting
me! Right?

791
01:36:16,051 --> 01:36:17,920
But you're here.
Why?

792
01:36:18,121 --> 01:36:20,450
Akash, you don't know Rohit.

793
01:36:20,761 --> 01:36:22,920
He doesn't like me meeting
any boys

794
01:36:25,761 --> 01:36:26,990
But Rohit is a good guy

795
01:36:27,931 --> 01:36:32,800
He has a few faults but then,
don't we all. Me... you...

796
01:36:33,741 --> 01:36:35,730
Faults... and me!

797
01:36:38,340 --> 01:36:39,699
So tell me about yourself

798
01:36:41,280 --> 01:36:42,139
What do you want to know?

799
01:36:48,320 --> 01:36:51,409
Of course I have. But not for
more than 2 weeks

800
01:36:52,550 --> 01:36:54,749
Then there's another girlfriend...
another 2 weeks...

801
01:36:55,620 --> 01:36:56,419
And then another...

802
01:36:56,620 --> 01:37:00,559
stop! I understand how your
girlfriend system works

803
01:37:00,930 --> 01:37:02,759
What I don't understand is...
why?

804
01:37:04,130 --> 01:37:07,529
The fact is, I've seen many of my
friends with their "beloveds"

805
01:37:07,970 --> 01:37:10,329
They have everything but love
for each other

806
01:37:11,969 --> 01:37:13,458
That's why I think I am better off
as I am

807
01:37:13,739 --> 01:37:16,708
No questions... no answers

808
01:37:18,179 --> 01:37:20,908
I don't ask Rohit questions,
nor do I demand answers

809
01:37:21,119 --> 01:37:23,678
But he asks questions.
He demands answers

810
01:37:25,019 --> 01:37:27,348
I never said it's always
the girl's fault

811
01:37:28,059 --> 01:37:31,388
But relationships just get like that.
Start with joy and end in grief

812
01:37:32,459 --> 01:37:36,418
I see! So this is the result of
an end in grief

813
01:37:37,829 --> 01:37:39,598
Now I've understood your
2 weeks formula!

814
01:37:39,799 --> 01:37:40,928
No! It's nothing of the sort

815
01:37:41,669 --> 01:37:44,638
I have consciously decided not to
fall in love and ruin my life

816
01:37:46,168 --> 01:37:48,967
But love isn't about decisions.
It just happens

817
01:37:49,678 --> 01:37:50,637
Then I don't let it happen to me

818
01:37:51,848 --> 01:37:54,137
Give it some time. I'm sure
it will some day

819
01:37:56,678 --> 01:37:59,307
Why? Are you proposing?

820
01:38:08,858 --> 01:38:09,987
How was your day?

821
01:38:14,538 --> 01:38:15,327
Akash is nuts

822
01:38:39,127 --> 01:38:40,586
Turn it down guys.
It's my wife-to-be

823
01:38:43,457 --> 01:38:44,086
How are you?

824
01:38:44,797 --> 01:38:46,096
Hopefully a little less drunk

825
01:38:48,967 --> 01:38:50,936
Did you get my message?
Where were you?

826
01:38:51,967 --> 01:38:53,096
I met Akash for lunch

827
01:38:57,136 --> 01:39:00,595
I told you not to meet him!
Why don't you listen to me?

828
01:39:03,316 --> 01:39:05,105
Are you yelling at me in front
of your friends?

829
01:39:10,656 --> 01:39:14,115
I am coming there. It'll take some
time but I will be there

830
01:39:15,826 --> 01:39:18,125
As you wish, Rohit. Bye

831
01:39:24,766 --> 01:39:28,065
Pooja, I was in the neighbourhood
and I thought...

832
01:39:29,935 --> 01:39:32,234
Pooja, if you aren't doing
anything else...

833
01:39:35,115 --> 01:39:37,574
Pooja, I was in the neighbour...

834
01:39:39,445 --> 01:39:40,744
Bye mom, I'll call later

835
01:40:22,324 --> 01:40:23,623
Fine. And you?

836
01:40:26,994 --> 01:40:29,463
Subodh, this is Sameer.
Sameer, this is Subodh

837
01:40:40,673 --> 01:40:41,802
Are you waiting for someone?

838
01:40:42,513 --> 01:40:45,812
Yes. But it seems like
they won't show up now

839
01:40:53,083 --> 01:40:55,212
So tell me... what's the plan
after dinner?

840
01:40:56,263 --> 01:40:56,882
No plan

841
01:40:58,763 --> 01:40:59,882
Come on, let's do something

842
01:41:02,263 --> 01:41:02,892
What say, Subodh?

843
01:41:03,933 --> 01:41:05,732
I'm sorry. I've made it a habit
to sleep by 10

844
01:41:07,933 --> 01:41:09,732
One night won't change
your habit

845
01:41:10,443 --> 01:41:12,412
Come on, pal. Anyway,
it's Sunday tomorrow

846
01:41:12,772 --> 01:41:15,571
I know. Thing is I've to wake up at
5 and do Yoga

847
01:41:16,282 --> 01:41:19,251
Then some jogging and breakfast
at 8 sharp

848
01:41:20,612 --> 01:41:21,581
And since it's Sunday...

849
01:41:22,122 --> 01:41:23,911
...we spend the day at Kumar uncle's
beach house

850
01:41:27,222 --> 01:41:27,691
I'll be right back

851
01:41:33,932 --> 01:41:35,391
It's time for his bathroom break,
right?

852
01:41:36,102 --> 01:41:38,391
He isn't that bad

853
01:41:42,442 --> 01:41:43,731
So where are you off to?

854
01:41:44,442 --> 01:41:44,901
Let's see...

855
01:41:45,772 --> 01:41:49,901
If Time Table doesn't want to
come, may be you can join me

856
01:41:51,111 --> 01:41:52,080
I'm sure I can...

857
01:41:59,451 --> 01:42:00,750
If I call you sometime...

858
01:42:18,701 --> 01:42:21,170
Wow! What're we celebrating?

859
01:42:22,380 --> 01:42:22,999
You don't remember?

860
01:42:24,380 --> 01:42:28,179
It was on this day five months ago
that I told you what I felt for you

861
01:42:41,960 --> 01:42:43,589
To Subodh and Pooja!

862
01:42:49,800 --> 01:42:51,269
What's the situation like?
- Pretty intense

863
01:42:55,639 --> 01:42:56,268
Really, Mahesh

864
01:42:57,639 --> 01:43:01,598
There were such intense scenes
in the film! So moving...

865
01:43:03,149 --> 01:43:04,118
Please cut out the performance

866
01:43:04,479 --> 01:43:07,608
And forgive me for taking you
to see such a good film!

867
01:43:08,989 --> 01:43:10,108
You see! That's my biggest problem

868
01:43:10,989 --> 01:43:12,288
I can't bear watching good films

869
01:43:13,659 --> 01:43:17,288
Yes. You only like those
wham bang action films

870
01:43:17,829 --> 01:43:19,298
Anyway, that's all you can
understand...

871
01:43:19,829 --> 01:43:22,628
...because they don't require you
to use your brains or heart!

872
01:43:23,669 --> 01:43:25,468
You need plenty of brains for
these love stories

873
01:43:26,339 --> 01:43:28,968
She sits here shedding tears,
he sits there sighing...

874
01:43:30,178 --> 01:43:31,467
...what's all this lovey- dovey
stuff about anyway!

875
01:43:33,008 --> 01:43:33,807
You won't understand

876
01:43:35,678 --> 01:43:36,807
What're you doing man, let's go

877
01:43:56,538 --> 01:43:59,837
Wonder why
people fall in love

878
01:44:04,208 --> 01:44:07,507
Wonder why people
are ready to die for someone

879
01:44:11,717 --> 01:44:15,016
Wonder why
people fall in love

880
01:44:15,557 --> 01:44:18,846
Wonder why people
are ready to die for someone

881
01:44:19,557 --> 01:44:23,516
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why...

882
01:44:27,227 --> 01:44:30,686
Wonder why... why... why!

883
01:44:35,407 --> 01:44:39,036
Just think about it,
there is only grief in love

884
01:44:40,406 --> 01:44:44,035
As for love's cruelty,
it's past counting

885
01:44:45,416 --> 01:44:49,545
When in love
your head must remain bowed

886
01:44:50,586 --> 01:44:54,715
Even when in pain
you have to smile

887
01:44:54,926 --> 01:44:58,055
Why fill your own life
with poison?

888
01:45:02,436 --> 01:45:05,725
Wonder why
people fall in love

889
01:45:07,766 --> 01:45:11,225
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why

890
01:45:12,776 --> 01:45:16,405
Wonder why why... why...

891
01:45:21,445 --> 01:45:27,584
Without love
what's left in life

892
01:45:28,955 --> 01:45:35,754
Without love
A person is Ionely

893
01:45:40,305 --> 01:45:43,604
Without love
what's there in life

894
01:45:44,135 --> 01:45:47,264
Without love
A person is Ionely

895
01:45:47,974 --> 01:45:51,103
Love brings colour
into your life

896
01:45:51,644 --> 01:45:54,943
Love brings beauty
into your life

897
01:45:55,484 --> 01:45:58,783
People fall in love
but hide it

898
01:46:02,994 --> 01:46:06,283
Wonder why they fear
expressing it openly

899
01:46:08,324 --> 01:46:11,783
Wonder why,
Oh wonder why...

900
01:46:13,164 --> 01:46:16,793
Wonder why why why!

901
01:47:04,712 --> 01:47:07,341
Love is just
needless trouble

902
01:47:09,552 --> 01:47:12,521
Love is beautiful
in every aspect

903
01:47:14,062 --> 01:47:17,511
We are all better off
far away from love

904
01:47:19,402 --> 01:47:22,521
Love's every form
is the assured truth

905
01:47:22,902 --> 01:47:27,201
He that tests love's
waters...

906
01:47:27,902 --> 01:47:31,031
...neither drowns nor floats

907
01:47:31,741 --> 01:47:34,040
Wonder why?

908
01:47:34,241 --> 01:47:37,370
Everyone but everyone
falls in love

909
01:47:37,751 --> 01:47:41,550
Wonder why only you
keep avoiding it

910
01:47:41,751 --> 01:47:45,550
Wonder why...

911
01:47:45,761 --> 01:47:47,880
Wonder why...

912
01:47:49,431 --> 01:47:53,380
Wonder why why why!

913
01:48:27,330 --> 01:48:28,129
Tell me something Shalini

914
01:48:29,160 --> 01:48:30,629
Why're you so scared of
sitting on these rides?

915
01:48:31,500 --> 01:48:32,299
I m not scared

916
01:48:33,670 --> 01:48:38,299
I think only those who aren't right
in their heads enjoy these rides

917
01:48:41,009 --> 01:48:41,638
Interesting excuse

918
01:48:42,509 --> 01:48:44,638
You need courage to sit on
these rides! You need guts

919
01:48:45,849 --> 01:48:48,148
But don't worry. There are many
cowards like you around here

920
01:48:49,349 --> 01:48:50,648
Look. There's one right there

921
01:48:55,519 --> 01:48:56,488
It's not like that at all

922
01:48:57,189 --> 01:49:01,318
If it isn't like that, then get on
that ride with me

923
01:49:06,369 --> 01:49:07,498
Why? No guts?

924
01:49:09,539 --> 01:49:10,158
It's getting late

925
01:49:16,048 --> 01:49:17,507
I'm going on that ride

926
01:49:18,218 --> 01:49:21,517
If you want, you can come with me.
Or sit here and get bored

927
01:49:27,958 --> 01:49:30,587
Absolutely no guts

928
01:50:29,746 --> 01:50:31,715
Hurry. We can catch this train

929
01:52:51,392 --> 01:52:53,511
Really Shalini! How could you
scare that poor old man!

930
01:53:08,772 --> 01:53:09,901
How did it go?

931
01:53:10,772 --> 01:53:13,401
Really well. They like my work

932
01:53:13,782 --> 01:53:17,231
And... they want me to
come back

933
01:53:18,281 --> 01:53:19,250
That's great

934
01:53:20,121 --> 01:53:21,080
When will you have to go?

935
01:53:21,781 --> 01:53:24,080
I've just returned and you're
asking about my leaving

936
01:53:26,961 --> 01:53:28,250
Did you talk to Sameer?

937
01:53:28,621 --> 01:53:29,250
No. Why?

938
01:53:29,961 --> 01:53:32,930
He came over the morning
you left

939
01:53:33,291 --> 01:53:34,590
He seemed very troubled

940
01:53:36,631 --> 01:53:39,600
What did he say?
- Nothing

941
01:53:49,141 --> 01:53:51,610
When did you get back?

942
01:53:55,150 --> 01:53:56,779
How are you? How's everything?

943
01:53:56,990 --> 01:53:58,449
Great. How are things with you
man?

944
01:53:58,820 --> 01:54:00,449
It's a very long story

945
01:54:00,820 --> 01:54:01,949
Let's go up and talk

946
01:54:06,790 --> 01:54:09,259
Okay, so here's the situation

947
01:54:10,630 --> 01:54:12,759
You are pretty good friends.
Hang out together

948
01:54:13,470 --> 01:54:14,929
But you still haven't told her
how you feel

949
01:54:16,640 --> 01:54:17,759
I've tried very hard...

950
01:54:21,140 --> 01:54:22,439
But the words just don't come out

951
01:54:26,649 --> 01:54:27,768
Didn't she have a boyfriend?

952
01:54:29,819 --> 01:54:31,438
Yup. She did... but not anymore

953
01:54:32,649 --> 01:54:34,448
I don't know what Pooja saw
in him

954
01:54:34,989 --> 01:54:37,458
I mean he was sweet
but what a bore!

955
01:54:39,989 --> 01:54:42,958
One day I made the mistake of
going for a drive with them

956
01:54:45,029 --> 01:54:45,998
See this place...

957
01:54:46,699 --> 01:54:49,328
I met Pooja for the first time
on 15th September right here

958
01:54:52,539 --> 01:54:55,998
Exactly 7 days later, we came here
to have ice cream... 22nd September

959
01:54:59,709 --> 01:55:01,008
You wouldn't remember the time,
would you?

960
01:55:01,548 --> 01:55:04,846
Of course I remember.
It was exactly 5.55

961
01:55:11,722 --> 01:55:14,010
That's not all

962
01:55:14,891 --> 01:55:18,009
He'd buy her a balloon
everyday

963
01:55:18,389 --> 01:55:19,008
Balloon...?

964
01:55:20,058 --> 01:55:24,515
Yes. You know those heart shaped
ones you get at signals

965
01:55:28,064 --> 01:55:30,522
It's okay but...
Everyday!

966
01:55:30,893 --> 01:55:31,692
One balloon a day!

967
01:55:37,200 --> 01:55:39,169
I knew the guy was deranged

968
01:55:49,374 --> 01:55:53,002
If you love Pooja so much,
why haven't you told her?

969
01:55:56,040 --> 01:55:57,169
I was afraid...

970
01:55:59,039 --> 01:56:02,007
What if Pooja says no?

971
01:56:03,876 --> 01:56:07,004
I'd even lose this friendship
we share now...

972
01:56:07,884 --> 01:56:08,843
and be all alone

973
01:56:13,881 --> 01:56:16,679
You weren't here.
Nor was Akash

974
01:56:23,217 --> 01:56:24,186
Anyway, you're here now

975
01:56:25,056 --> 01:56:27,025
And I feel stronger knowing
that you're here for me

976
01:56:28,394 --> 01:56:29,683
I'm always here for you, Sameer

977
01:56:33,722 --> 01:56:34,521
Then... shall I tell her today?

978
01:56:37,400 --> 01:56:38,019
Tell her

979
01:56:41,728 --> 01:56:43,856
Pooja, there's something
I need to tell you

980
01:56:46,895 --> 01:56:51,522
I wonder what if the arranging
incident hadn't happened

981
01:56:54,241 --> 01:56:57,029
If we hadn't met the way we
did...

982
01:56:57,909 --> 01:57:01,197
If I had met you somewhere else,
would we be the same as we are now?

983
01:57:01,907 --> 01:57:04,875
And if we weren't the way we are,
how else would we be?

984
01:57:05,246 --> 01:57:06,705
If you thought differently
about me...

985
01:57:06,905 --> 01:57:09,033
...if I thought differently about
you, what'd happen?

986
01:57:11,143 --> 01:57:14,771
What's happening now?
...What am I saying?

987
01:57:16,650 --> 01:57:21,947
Just a lot of ifs!
What's the matter?

988
01:57:24,986 --> 01:57:26,115
The matter is just that...

989
01:57:28,324 --> 01:57:29,443
I'm falling in love with you

990
01:57:32,162 --> 01:57:34,450
I agree that we don't know
each other very well

991
01:57:41,498 --> 01:57:45,625
If you trust me at all, believe
that I am telling the truth

992
01:58:29,284 --> 01:58:34,241
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

993
01:58:34,451 --> 01:58:39,758
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

994
01:58:44,626 --> 01:58:46,924
She who loves only me

995
01:58:47,125 --> 01:58:49,423
She must be even ready
to say...

996
01:58:49,634 --> 01:58:51,922
"O listen, you are the one
who has my heart"

997
01:58:52,132 --> 01:58:54,930
Oh, where is that girl?

998
01:59:04,636 --> 01:59:09,593
She who lives in your dream
as love's beautiful embodiment...

999
01:59:09,804 --> 01:59:12,102
You will find her someday
or other

1000
01:59:12,312 --> 01:59:15,270
Just look here and there

1001
01:59:19,978 --> 01:59:22,276
Let's both go and find her...

1002
01:59:22,477 --> 01:59:24,775
This angel, this fairy,
this damsel so dainty...

1003
01:59:24,986 --> 01:59:27,274
...who upon seeing,
you will say

1004
01:59:27,485 --> 01:59:30,283
She is right here!

1005
02:00:05,666 --> 02:00:09,294
I wonder why
I had this thought...

1006
02:00:10,003 --> 02:00:15,630
Could you be the
dream girl?

1007
02:00:15,841 --> 02:00:25,306
You have all the graces
that I search for everywhere

1008
02:00:25,516 --> 02:00:27,974
I think you are deluded

1009
02:00:28,174 --> 02:00:30,472
I wonder what you think I am

1010
02:00:30,683 --> 02:00:32,981
I am no angel or fairy
nor any celestial nymph

1011
02:00:33,182 --> 02:00:36,150
Don't have any such
illusions

1012
02:00:40,848 --> 02:00:45,655
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

1013
02:00:45,856 --> 02:00:51,153
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

1014
02:01:26,545 --> 02:01:30,503
Suppose I say to you...

1015
02:01:30,713 --> 02:01:36,510
All I think of
is you and only you

1016
02:01:36,710 --> 02:01:40,668
You must know
this is what I desire...

1017
02:01:40,878 --> 02:01:46,345
...you must be with me,
only with me

1018
02:01:46,555 --> 02:01:48,843
Oh, what have you made me believe!

1019
02:01:49,054 --> 02:01:51,352
Oh, how you make my heart beat!

1020
02:01:51,553 --> 02:01:53,851
You melt my body and soul...

1021
02:01:54,051 --> 02:01:56,849
...reciting this saga of yours

1022
02:02:06,725 --> 02:02:11,522
I look everywhere for her.
But I still haven't found her

1023
02:02:11,733 --> 02:02:14,531
Where is the girl
in whose love I can believe?

1024
02:02:14,731 --> 02:02:19,188
Oh, where is that girl?
That girl is here!

1025
02:02:19,399 --> 02:02:35,371
Where is that girl?
- That girl is here!

1026
02:03:03,087 --> 02:03:06,055
I can't believe that it's already
time for you to leave

1027
02:03:08,095 --> 02:03:10,064
Don't worry, Mom.
I'll be back soon

1028
02:03:10,593 --> 02:03:12,062
Three months is not soon

1029
02:03:13,592 --> 02:03:14,721
And that's this time

1030
02:03:16,600 --> 02:03:18,559
You don't know how long
you'll be gone next time

1031
02:03:21,598 --> 02:03:25,895
Siddharth... have you thought about
marriage?

1032
02:03:26,106 --> 02:03:26,725
Mom!

1033
02:03:28,604 --> 02:03:29,573
What Mom!

1034
02:03:32,103 --> 02:03:35,401
Some other time, okay?
- But why? Why not now?

1035
02:03:39,279 --> 02:03:43,906
It's just... forget it, Mom.
You won't understand

1036
02:03:46,615 --> 02:03:49,733
I'm your mother! If I can't
understand you, who else will?

1037
02:03:52,782 --> 02:03:53,901
Is there someone you like?

1038
02:03:59,289 --> 02:04:01,248
Sid, what's the matter?

1039
02:04:02,287 --> 02:04:03,916
You've never hidden anything
from me

1040
02:04:04,117 --> 02:04:06,585
Yes, Ma. But there are some things
that you just can't tell somebody

1041
02:04:06,955 --> 02:04:08,084
Yes there are...

1042
02:04:08,794 --> 02:04:12,082
But I can see there's something
eating away at you inside

1043
02:04:12,462 --> 02:04:14,580
Will you keep it bottled up inside
all your life?

1044
02:04:21,958 --> 02:04:23,587
Ma, I'm telling you
you won't understand!

1045
02:04:24,466 --> 02:04:25,585
Why won't I understand?

1046
02:04:26,965 --> 02:04:28,434
Try telling me

1047
02:04:32,133 --> 02:04:34,761
What is this thing that I don't
have the right to know?

1048
02:04:39,139 --> 02:04:39,758
What's the matter?

1049
02:04:52,143 --> 02:04:53,112
That Tara Jaiswal?

1050
02:04:55,881 --> 02:04:58,009
I've met her so many times...
But... she...

1051
02:05:00,718 --> 02:05:01,837
When did this start?

1052
02:05:03,047 --> 02:05:04,516
I don't know when...

1053
02:05:06,555 --> 02:05:08,174
I won't let you ruin your life!

1054
02:05:09,054 --> 02:05:11,182
Have you any inkling of what
you are saying?

1055
02:05:12,392 --> 02:05:14,351
My son has fallen in love with
a woman who...

1056
02:05:15,051 --> 02:05:16,680
You were right I wouldn't
understand

1057
02:05:18,219 --> 02:05:20,847
And what has she told you,
that she loves you?

1058
02:05:21,228 --> 02:05:23,856
She must've seduced you with her
sad stories

1059
02:05:24,496 --> 02:05:25,615
What did she say to you?
- She said nothing!

1060
02:05:32,163 --> 02:05:33,132
She doesn't even know that I...

1061
02:05:42,507 --> 02:05:44,296
Your mother is absolutely right,
Siddharth

1062
02:05:45,336 --> 02:05:50,293
Don't ruin your life over me. And the
little peace I have left in my life...

1063
02:05:51,173 --> 02:05:53,301
Please don't take it away
from me

1064
02:06:13,422 --> 02:06:16,390
Go away! - Please listen to me

1065
02:06:16,590 --> 02:06:17,559
I don't want to hear anything

1066
02:06:18,589 --> 02:06:21,887
Have I ever made you feel
that I love you...

1067
02:06:22,088 --> 02:06:23,717
...or want a relationship
with you?

1068
02:06:25,426 --> 02:06:25,895
No

1069
02:06:26,595 --> 02:06:28,064
Then what made you think...

1070
02:06:28,594 --> 02:06:29,723
...that you and I could...

1071
02:06:30,264 --> 02:06:31,563
...have any such relationship?

1072
02:06:35,431 --> 02:06:37,060
This is the problem with your
generation

1073
02:06:38,100 --> 02:06:43,227
You all think anything goes.
But that's not so, Siddharth

1074
02:06:46,435 --> 02:06:48,234
Why just me?

1075
02:06:49,104 --> 02:06:50,403
You have also caused your mother
a lot of pain

1076
02:06:52,942 --> 02:06:53,731
Please sit down

1077
02:07:23,957 --> 02:07:27,255
I'm so sorry that I caused you
and my mother such pain

1078
02:07:31,293 --> 02:07:33,591
I'm sorry you had to hear
all this because of me

1079
02:07:37,130 --> 02:07:39,099
But it's true that I love you

1080
02:07:52,932 --> 02:07:56,230
It's also true that I never
wanted you to know it

1081
02:07:58,409 --> 02:07:59,868
Because I knew that you...

1082
02:08:01,908 --> 02:08:02,707
...would never be able to understand

1083
02:08:08,145 --> 02:08:09,614
I just want to see you happy

1084
02:08:14,481 --> 02:08:19,438
And if knowing the truth
has caused you pain today...

1085
02:08:22,148 --> 02:08:25,446
All I can say is, that wasn't
my intention

1086
02:08:37,830 --> 02:08:40,948
Sid, please leave now

1087
02:09:15,441 --> 02:09:16,240
After the workshop...

1088
02:09:18,949 --> 02:09:21,417
I think I'll go stay at uncle's
farm house for a while

1089
02:09:23,617 --> 02:09:25,086
It's a good place to paint

1090
02:09:35,451 --> 02:09:36,580
Will you come with me?

1091
02:09:40,628 --> 02:09:42,087
I don't want to go without you

1092
02:10:20,648 --> 02:10:21,267
Just a minute...

1093
02:11:17,710 --> 02:11:18,669
You look very lovely

1094
02:11:24,377 --> 02:11:26,675
So, why are we here?

1095
02:11:28,045 --> 02:11:31,843
To prove to you that a thing called
love does exist in this world

1096
02:11:35,051 --> 02:11:36,340
Don't you ever give up?

1097
02:11:37,550 --> 02:11:39,179
Shut up and lets go in

1098
02:12:07,235 --> 02:12:09,523
Why are we here?
- To watch an opera

1099
02:12:10,903 --> 02:12:11,692
Yes, but why?

1100
02:12:13,062 --> 02:12:14,531
You'll know when the time comes

1101
02:13:21,938 --> 02:13:24,226
The girl's name is Cressida
and the boy is Troilus

1102
02:13:25,766 --> 02:13:27,565
They love each other very much

1103
02:13:46,785 --> 02:13:48,244
But Troilus must go now

1104
02:13:49,614 --> 02:13:51,583
He has to go to war for his country

1105
02:13:53,452 --> 02:13:55,920
Cressida is afraid something may
happen to him

1106
02:13:58,120 --> 02:14:00,248
Troilus is telling her
nothing will happen to him

1107
02:15:21,498 --> 02:15:27,125
This is the spirit of Troilus...
standing at heaven's gate

1108
02:15:28,834 --> 02:15:30,303
But he doesn't want to go inside

1109
02:15:33,002 --> 02:15:34,801
He is asking God for one day

1110
02:15:37,340 --> 02:15:39,129
He wants to meet Cressida for
one last time

1111
02:15:41,178 --> 02:15:44,466
And tell her how much he loves her

1112
02:15:47,845 --> 02:15:49,474
If he is given one day...

1113
02:15:51,013 --> 02:15:53,141
He is willing to die a thousand
deaths

1114
02:16:01,188 --> 02:16:02,807
Shut your eyes, Akash

1115
02:16:08,854 --> 02:16:09,323
Think...

1116
02:16:10,853 --> 02:16:11,322
Who is it...

1117
02:16:13,022 --> 02:16:16,480
...to spend that one day with, you
are willing to die a thousand deaths

1118
02:16:19,189 --> 02:16:20,158
Who is it, Akash?

1119
02:17:57,510 --> 02:17:58,809
No so easily!

1120
02:18:00,339 --> 02:18:02,637
You still haven't told me
who you saw

1121
02:18:05,346 --> 02:18:06,815
You seem quite sure that I
saw someone?

1122
02:18:07,515 --> 02:18:09,314
Yes. Because today for
the first time...

1123
02:18:09,514 --> 02:18:11,812
...you're talking less
and thinking more!

1124
02:18:23,757 --> 02:18:24,376
Then listen

1125
02:18:26,756 --> 02:18:27,385
I saw her...

1126
02:18:29,754 --> 02:18:30,383
And I felt...

1127
02:18:30,594 --> 02:18:33,222
...perhaps this is what
they call love

1128
02:18:40,759 --> 02:18:41,888
I wanted to touch her...

1129
02:18:44,267 --> 02:18:45,566
...hold her in my arms...

1130
02:18:48,765 --> 02:18:51,563
I saw such innocence
in her eyes...

1131
02:18:54,432 --> 02:18:55,561
...like I see in your eyes now

1132
02:19:00,269 --> 02:19:01,398
Her voice...

1133
02:19:01,778 --> 02:19:03,397
...had the kind of magic
your voice has

1134
02:19:05,606 --> 02:19:09,404
I can still feel the fragrance
of her breath...

1135
02:19:09,614 --> 02:19:11,073
...like I can feel
in your breath now

1136
02:19:13,242 --> 02:19:14,041
Who was she?

1137
02:19:25,456 --> 02:19:26,575
That fat opera singer!

1138
02:19:44,627 --> 02:19:50,923
Shalini, come inside... at once!

1139
02:20:45,496 --> 02:20:47,115
I think the two of you should
talk alone

1140
02:20:56,601 --> 02:20:59,069
Where had you gone?
- To the opera

1141
02:21:01,328 --> 02:21:02,127
With Akash!

1142
02:21:03,997 --> 02:21:06,295
How many times have I told you
not to meet him!

1143
02:21:09,674 --> 02:21:12,972
Rohit, will you keep telling me
all my life...

1144
02:21:13,172 --> 02:21:14,641
...who I should or should not meet!

1145
02:21:18,010 --> 02:21:18,629
Yes. I will

1146
02:21:19,339 --> 02:21:22,637
And you will never see Akash
again. You got that?

1147
02:21:29,184 --> 02:21:32,302
Rohit, I need some time to think
and you need it too

1148
02:22:52,863 --> 02:22:56,151
Shalini had called.
She said it's important

1149
02:23:08,535 --> 02:23:10,334
Hi, Rohit. It's Akash

1150
02:23:11,863 --> 02:23:14,161
Is Shalini there? She had called

1151
02:23:14,702 --> 02:23:18,500
I know. We are going back...
to get married

1152
02:23:24,207 --> 02:23:25,176
Can I speak to Shalini?

1153
02:23:53,123 --> 02:23:54,592
That's good news

1154
02:23:57,220 --> 02:23:58,849
Akash, we are going back tomorrow

1155
02:24:00,229 --> 02:24:01,688
Can you come for dinner tonight?

1156
02:24:04,727 --> 02:24:06,855
I don't know. Bye

1157
02:24:24,237 --> 02:24:25,366
Hey, Akash! We thought you
weren't going to make it

1158
02:25:08,025 --> 02:25:10,393
They're beautiful. Thanks

1159
02:25:12,093 --> 02:25:12,782
What will you drink?

1160
02:25:14,532 --> 02:25:17,790
We can drink later. Let's eat first.
I'm starving

1161
02:25:44,777 --> 02:25:47,575
Shalini, have you told
Mahesh Uncle...

1162
02:25:47,775 --> 02:25:49,244
...how you and Akash met?

1163
02:25:53,282 --> 02:25:53,801
No?

1164
02:25:56,581 --> 02:25:57,740
Really, Mahesh Uncle...

1165
02:25:58,320 --> 02:26:00,578
I don't know what you'd have
done if you were there

1166
02:26:00,789 --> 02:26:01,908
What happened?

1167
02:26:03,717 --> 02:26:05,416
It was at my graduation
party

1168
02:26:06,086 --> 02:26:06,745
Shalini was with me

1169
02:26:06,956 --> 02:26:09,014
Perhaps Akash didn't know
that...

1170
02:26:19,289 --> 02:26:20,588
Sorry for the punch

1171
02:26:23,967 --> 02:26:26,425
No, Rohit. It was my fault

1172
02:26:29,464 --> 02:26:32,432
But to tell you the truth,
I think I was lucky

1173
02:26:33,772 --> 02:26:34,251
What do you mean?

1174
02:26:34,602 --> 02:26:38,160
I mean, if Shalini was with me...

1175
02:26:39,140 --> 02:26:41,268
...and someone had acted fresh...

1176
02:26:42,978 --> 02:26:44,267
I'd have killed him

1177
02:26:57,780 --> 02:26:58,269
That is...

1178
02:26:59,619 --> 02:27:01,108
If Shalini was with you

1179
02:27:34,002 --> 02:27:34,591
Hey, wait...

1180
02:27:55,571 --> 02:27:58,129
You're coming to our wedding,
aren't you?

1181
02:27:59,180 --> 02:28:01,978
No, I can't make it. There's a lot
of work to be done

1182
02:28:04,317 --> 02:28:05,306
Some friend you are!

1183
02:28:06,916 --> 02:28:09,474
Anyway, don't forget to call us to
your wedding

1184
02:28:10,314 --> 02:28:11,143
We'll definitely be there

1185
02:28:12,053 --> 02:28:13,812
I'm not going to get married

1186
02:28:14,552 --> 02:28:15,141
Why?

1187
02:28:18,090 --> 02:28:20,648
It's necessary to love someone
to get married

1188
02:28:21,518 --> 02:28:22,987
And I believe...

1189
02:28:23,357 --> 02:28:25,156
...this thing called love doesn't
exist in the world

1190
02:28:27,755 --> 02:28:29,454
Shalini and I love each other

1191
02:28:29,694 --> 02:28:31,493
That's why we're getting married.
Isn't that so, Shalini?

1192
02:28:34,862 --> 02:28:39,489
You both shouldn't ask each other
this question. Ask yourself

1193
02:28:45,536 --> 02:28:46,325
I better go

1194
02:29:19,819 --> 02:29:22,007
You left your jacket with me
the other night

1195
02:29:35,891 --> 02:29:40,848
Some day I want to tell you why
I am marrying Rohit

1196
02:29:41,059 --> 02:29:45,017
Why? What's the need to tell me?

1197
02:29:47,695 --> 02:29:48,524
I need to...

1198
02:29:49,864 --> 02:29:51,523
Because we both know...

1199
02:29:54,632 --> 02:29:56,531
...that night at the opera,
when you shut your eyes...

1200
02:29:57,870 --> 02:30:00,358
...it wasn't the fat opera singer
you saw

1201
02:30:26,756 --> 02:30:33,382
Loneliness

1202
02:30:36,521 --> 02:30:40,888
This Ioneliness...

1203
02:30:46,366 --> 02:30:51,063
Why have I stumbled on
the path of love

1204
02:30:51,364 --> 02:30:55,891
All my dreams lie shattered
A sense of gloom lies heavy

1205
02:30:56,101 --> 02:31:00,558
Every joy is be numbed

1206
02:31:00,939 --> 02:31:05,996
My very life is lost

1207
02:31:06,276 --> 02:31:10,973
I am being punished
for loving you

1208
02:31:11,174 --> 02:31:16,041
Loneliness...

1209
02:31:16,481 --> 02:31:20,778
Loneliness stretches over
miles and miles

1210
02:32:10,304 --> 02:32:15,761
In my dream I saw
a hand in my hand

1211
02:32:20,309 --> 02:32:25,936
Now I am blinded by the
shards of a shattered dream

1212
02:32:40,149 --> 02:32:44,606
Someone was here yesterday

1213
02:32:44,827 --> 02:32:49,914
but today there is no one

1214
02:32:50,324 --> 02:32:55,121
Like a cobra's venomous hiss
it envelopes my very breath...

1215
02:32:55,332 --> 02:32:59,989
...this Ioneliness

1216
02:33:00,369 --> 02:33:04,556
has brought tears to my eyes

1217
02:33:54,522 --> 02:33:59,979
Oh how could my hope for
something be so futile

1218
02:34:04,457 --> 02:34:10,264
I've embarked on a journey
to which there is no destination

1219
02:34:24,037 --> 02:34:28,334
Where should I go?

1220
02:34:28,705 --> 02:34:33,802
To whom shall I explain?

1221
02:34:34,242 --> 02:34:36,330
What I had wanted...

1222
02:34:36,541 --> 02:34:38,839
And why I ended up with...

1223
02:34:39,050 --> 02:34:44,007
...this Ioneliness

1224
02:34:44,217 --> 02:34:48,344
Loneliness
deeply dark as the night

1225
02:34:58,860 --> 02:35:03,687
Why have I stumbled on
the path of love

1226
02:35:03,887 --> 02:35:08,324
All my dreams lie shattered
A sense of gloom lies heavy

1227
02:35:08,525 --> 02:35:13,192
Every joy is be numbed

1228
02:35:13,393 --> 02:35:18,700
My very life is lost

1229
02:35:19,000 --> 02:35:23,527
I am being punished
for loving you

1230
02:35:23,737 --> 02:35:28,394
Loneliness...

1231
02:35:28,905 --> 02:35:33,202
Loneliness stretches over
miles and miles

1232
02:36:20,429 --> 02:36:21,658
Hello, Aunty. Is Sameer home?

1233
02:36:21,998 --> 02:36:22,727
Who is this?

1234
02:36:26,636 --> 02:36:29,564
You want to talk to Sameer
and you've called Siddharth!

1235
02:36:30,634 --> 02:36:31,393
How are you?

1236
02:36:32,073 --> 02:36:33,902
I... I'm okay, Aunty

1237
02:36:34,502 --> 02:36:38,400
He's gone to Kasauli. Give me
your number. I'll give it to him

1238
02:36:40,069 --> 02:36:42,068
No, it's okay.
I'll call him

1239
02:37:36,101 --> 02:37:36,860
How are you, son?

1240
02:37:40,899 --> 02:37:41,558
I'm okay, Dad

1241
02:37:44,037 --> 02:37:47,335
What's wrong? Are you unwell?

1242
02:37:48,675 --> 02:37:49,694
No, it's nothing like that

1243
02:37:51,114 --> 02:37:52,443
Been working all day...

1244
02:37:52,813 --> 02:37:53,602
I'm tired, that's all

1245
02:38:05,916 --> 02:38:07,545
Come back home, Akash

1246
02:38:36,361 --> 02:38:37,300
What's wrong, Akash?

1247
02:38:39,570 --> 02:38:41,469
I've never seen you like this
before

1248
02:38:42,668 --> 02:38:43,727
I'm in love, Dad

1249
02:38:46,906 --> 02:38:49,594
So what's the problem?

1250
02:38:51,134 --> 02:38:52,623
She is marrying somebody else

1251
02:38:56,841 --> 02:38:59,309
Have you told her you love her?

1252
02:39:01,449 --> 02:39:01,928
No

1253
02:39:03,448 --> 02:39:04,877
Does she love you?

1254
02:39:09,315 --> 02:39:10,074
Yes, she does

1255
02:39:12,823 --> 02:39:13,942
Has she told you?

1256
02:39:20,159 --> 02:39:24,646
Akash, you must tell her
how you feel

1257
02:39:27,296 --> 02:39:27,755
No

1258
02:39:28,565 --> 02:39:29,154
Why not?

1259
02:39:32,563 --> 02:39:33,992
She is marrying somebody else

1260
02:39:38,030 --> 02:39:42,327
There are many things in this world
that are beyond our understanding

1261
02:39:43,498 --> 02:39:45,327
When a person decides something...

1262
02:39:46,536 --> 02:39:49,664
...there must be a reason for that
decision

1263
02:39:50,804 --> 02:39:56,031
You say that the girl loves you
but is marrying someone else

1264
02:39:57,371 --> 02:40:01,668
Have you tried to find out
why she's doing it?

1265
02:40:04,147 --> 02:40:06,235
What's the reason for her decision?

1266
02:40:25,417 --> 02:40:26,356
How's Shalini?

1267
02:40:28,185 --> 02:40:28,914
She isn't happy

1268
02:40:31,054 --> 02:40:32,023
And how could she be?

1269
02:40:33,193 --> 02:40:36,161
She is marrying Rohit
but loves you

1270
02:40:40,329 --> 02:40:41,988
Did she tell you that?
- No

1271
02:40:44,327 --> 02:40:46,056
Did you ever tell me you love her?

1272
02:40:51,534 --> 02:40:53,293
Then why's she getting married?

1273
02:40:56,101 --> 02:40:58,589
Rohit's father and Shalini's father
were business partners

1274
02:41:00,909 --> 02:41:05,836
Shalini was six when her parents
were killed in a car accident

1275
02:41:07,546 --> 02:41:12,443
I was her only relative but
I wasn't able to support her

1276
02:41:15,542 --> 02:41:16,771
Rohit's parents took her in...

1277
02:41:16,981 --> 02:41:17,540
...not only into their home

1278
02:41:17,751 --> 02:41:19,680
but their hearts and their life

1279
02:41:20,949 --> 02:41:22,438
They've done a lot for her

1280
02:41:23,548 --> 02:41:27,546
If they want her to marry Rohit,
Shalini can't refuse

1281
02:41:30,084 --> 02:41:31,313
What else can she do?

1282
02:41:33,093 --> 02:41:36,651
On one hand are the people who've
given her the life she's living

1283
02:41:38,160 --> 02:41:39,089
On the other hand is a man...

1284
02:41:39,290 --> 02:41:41,988
She doesn't even know if he loves
her or not

1285
02:41:43,158 --> 02:41:47,825
Akash, what are you doing man!
Go and tell her you love her

1286
02:41:51,494 --> 02:41:53,463
Akash, only you know what
you have to do

1287
02:41:54,962 --> 02:41:57,090
Just know this. Tonight is
the Sangeet function...

1288
02:41:58,430 --> 02:41:59,629
...and tomorrow the wedding

1289
02:42:01,909 --> 02:42:04,767
Whatever your decision,
you must make it today

1290
02:44:19,600 --> 02:44:20,659
Will you marry me?

1291
02:44:30,145 --> 02:44:32,773
Not even if I tell you that
I love you?

1292
02:45:14,163 --> 02:45:14,722
Shalini...

1293
02:45:16,731 --> 02:45:18,789
I love you and only you

1294
02:45:21,339 --> 02:45:22,358
My every breath...

1295
02:45:24,038 --> 02:45:25,127
...every heartbeat...

1296
02:45:26,906 --> 02:45:29,494
...every moment,
is for you, Shalini

1297
02:45:32,343 --> 02:45:37,500
I'm sure that I was born
so that I could love you

1298
02:45:39,010 --> 02:45:41,638
And you were born to become mine

1299
02:45:42,948 --> 02:45:44,307
You are mine, Shalini

1300
02:45:45,377 --> 02:45:47,146
And if you ask your heart...

1301
02:45:48,285 --> 02:45:51,373
...you will know that I speak
the truth

1302
02:45:58,350 --> 02:46:00,978
What's going on! Who is this boy?

1303
02:46:01,359 --> 02:46:02,148
I'll tell you

1304
02:46:03,358 --> 02:46:07,056
He is Akash Malhotra,
A.K. Malhotra's son...

1305
02:46:07,726 --> 02:46:09,984
...who's been after Shalini,
wagging his tail

1306
02:46:10,964 --> 02:46:14,652
I hit him once but I guess
it wasn't enough, huh?

1307
02:46:15,732 --> 02:46:16,851
I won't leave you today!

1308
02:46:17,061 --> 02:46:22,298
You will do no such thing, Rohit.
I want to speak to Shalini first

1309
02:46:51,584 --> 02:46:54,342
No, Rohit! You wait here.
- But Dad! This is my life...

1310
02:48:13,093 --> 02:48:16,751
Mahesh, I feel very hurt today

1311
02:48:17,931 --> 02:48:20,619
I always thought that Shalini was
my daughter

1312
02:48:21,529 --> 02:48:24,557
But today I feel that she has
never thought of us as her own

1313
02:48:26,796 --> 02:48:29,694
She wants to repay her debt to us
by marrying Rohit

1314
02:48:32,234 --> 02:48:32,723
All right

1315
02:48:36,102 --> 02:48:39,130
Shalini, you must repay us

1316
02:48:40,869 --> 02:48:44,567
For looking after you from
childhood till now... you owe us

1317
02:48:45,407 --> 02:48:48,235
For giving you whatever you
asked for... you owe us

1318
02:48:49,505 --> 02:48:52,443
For shielding you from
even a hint of trouble...

1319
02:48:52,543 --> 02:48:53,372
...you owe us

1320
02:48:55,442 --> 02:48:59,609
Now if you want to repay all that
you owe us... see us happy...

1321
02:49:02,578 --> 02:49:04,107
Then marry Akash

1322
02:49:10,924 --> 02:49:12,443
Can you do this much for me?

1323
02:49:32,593 --> 02:49:33,222
Come...

1324
02:49:44,567 --> 02:49:48,664
Take care of her.
She is my daughter

1325
02:50:24,188 --> 02:50:24,947
Just a minute, Dad

1326
02:50:27,326 --> 02:50:30,084
You can't do this! Mom, why
aren't you saying anything?

1327
02:50:30,724 --> 02:50:32,623
Let her go, Rohit

1328
02:50:35,932 --> 02:50:39,120
You care about Shalini's happiness
but don't give a damn about mine!

1329
02:50:39,430 --> 02:50:43,887
Rohit, if Shalini is not happy
being with you...

1330
02:50:44,537 --> 02:50:46,026
...how can you ever be happy?

1331
02:50:48,166 --> 02:50:49,325
This can't happen to me!

1332
02:50:53,073 --> 02:50:54,232
I won't allow this!

1333
02:50:57,641 --> 02:50:58,130
What are you doing?

1334
02:51:33,493 --> 02:51:35,112
I love Akash

1335
02:51:56,172 --> 02:51:57,401
All his life he said...

1336
02:51:57,701 --> 02:51:59,400
I won't say "I love you" to anyone

1337
02:51:59,840 --> 02:52:00,829
And when he had to say it...

1338
02:52:01,169 --> 02:52:04,037
It was at someone's wedding
in front of 300 people!

1339
02:52:08,346 --> 02:52:09,395
Did you call him?

1340
02:52:13,213 --> 02:52:14,042
What did he say?

1341
02:52:17,081 --> 02:52:18,070
He wasn't home

1342
02:52:23,748 --> 02:52:25,477
I told you he won't come

1343
02:54:18,810 --> 02:54:20,799
Can I talk to Sid?

1344
02:54:42,649 --> 02:54:43,421
How are you?

1345
02:54:45,227 --> 02:54:47,032
Fine. How are you?

1346
02:54:53,764 --> 02:54:54,927
Forgive me

1347
02:54:57,886 --> 02:54:59,410
I must apologise too

1348
02:55:00,655 --> 02:55:04,507
Some other time.
It's my turn today

1349
02:55:06,985 --> 02:55:08,248
You haven't changed
at all

1350
02:55:09,092 --> 02:55:13,044
Ya. Anyway, it's hard to improve
on perfection

1351
02:55:19,374 --> 02:55:20,738
Where are you? When can we meet?

1352
02:55:22,213 --> 02:55:25,824
Today. Now. This very moment

1353
02:57:04,475 --> 02:57:08,618
Now... there's no pain...
nor any fear

1354
02:57:13,112 --> 02:57:14,606
I feel good

1355
02:57:17,025 --> 02:57:18,018
It's peaceful here

1356
02:57:22,652 --> 02:57:24,788
You're a good boy, Siddharth

1357
02:57:28,842 --> 02:57:30,547
You always stood by me

1358
02:57:35,232 --> 02:57:36,897
You want me to be happy,
don't you...

1359
02:57:40,830 --> 02:57:41,993
Then... you be happy

1360
02:57:44,842 --> 02:57:45,604
You will, won't you?

1361
02:57:45,986 --> 02:57:46,537
I will

1362
02:57:57,532 --> 02:57:58,966
Life is so strange

1363
02:58:01,214 --> 02:58:02,618
Some relationships...

1364
02:58:05,828 --> 02:58:07,463
...don't have any name

1365
02:58:14,295 --> 02:58:16,331
You and I will always...

1366
03:00:13,561 --> 03:00:16,259
Hey Sid, look at your ship

1367
03:00:17,272 --> 03:00:19,769
It was so small 2 years ago.
Look how much it's grown

1368
03:00:23,071 --> 03:00:26,070
If you guys wanted to be by
yourselves, you should've told us

1369
03:00:29,320 --> 03:00:32,058
See! I'm getting told off because
of you

1370
03:00:32,270 --> 03:00:33,263
I've been telling you, let's go

1371
03:00:33,544 --> 03:00:34,035
What?

1372
03:00:34,717 --> 03:00:35,609
Come on

1373
03:01:04,000 --> 03:01:04,802
Come on man
